messageBody:
On Fri, Jan 2, 2009 at 6:42 PM, abd elrahman mahmoud
<abdelrahman_mahmoud2004@...> wrote:
> hii all,
> am new in testing implementation so i need some help i just wrote a simple
> code( by eclipse ) & i dont know why there is an error & i cant fix it or
> understand this error althoug i attached the 2 JAR folder( Junit.jar &
> htmlUnit.jar )so i need any help plzzz i have to learn htmlunit within a
> week & i have to do it quickly thanks.....

I see that you basically made the same request a few weeks ago. At
that time I suggested some search engine terms that could bring you
information. Did you try those? I seem to recall quite a few good
JUnit tutorials available on the web and I'd be very surprised if
there weren't good tutorials forHtmlUnit also. As you were very
interested in HtmlUnit, did you try asking questions on their mailing
list? Have you tried the JUnit FAQ?

http://junit.sourceforge.net/doc/faq/faq.htm

If you have an error that you don't understand, have you tried
reducing the code down to the simplest possible state and seeing if
that works?

I suggest that you read Eric Raymond's guide to asking questions as
you have provided no actual information to help us help you. Trying to
send attached JAR files of JUnit and HtmlUnit won't help as we most
likely all already have those and the mailing list server will reject
them.

http://www.catb.org/~esr/faqs/smart-questions.html

What versions are you trying to use? What version of Java do you have
installed? What operating system are you using? We now know that you
are using Eclipse, but which version? Is the error in your test or is
the error in your code that you are testing, or both? Consider posting
a fragment of code that is giving you problems and you'll stand a much
better chance of receiving help.

Simon
(One of the JUnit mailing list moderators)
